Description: Orchestrate parallel AI agents in isolated git worktrees
 arduis is a lightweight GNOME desktop app that runs several AI coding
 agents (Claude Code) in parallel — each in its own git worktree, with
 real embedded VTE terminals. It is the Linux, terminal-centric answer
 for developers who live in the terminal and use AI agents heavily.
 .
 Each agent runs in an isolated worktree with a real PTY-backed terminal,
 letting you manage N agents at once and always know which one is waiting
 on you. Uses the system VTE (no bundling, no sandbox).
